## Summary
- add redacted policy evidence for the named `exec-approvals.json` artifact
- add `execApprovals` policy rules for required file presence, default security, scoped per-agent effective security, and allowlist pattern drift
- document top-level and scoped policy examples, plus focused scanner/doctor/conformance coverage

## Policy example
```jsonc
{
  "execApprovals": {
    "requireFile": true,
    "defaults": {
      // Security modes: "deny", "allowlist", or "full".
      // This default permits only the locked-down deny posture.
      "allowSecurity": ["deny"]
    }
  },
  "scopes": {
    "restricted-shell": {
      "agentIds": ["family-agent", "groups-agent"],
      "execApprovals": {
        "agents": {
          // Selected agents may use reviewed allowlist posture, but not "full".
          "allowSecurity": ["allowlist"],
          "allowlist": {
            "expected": [
              "travel-hub",
              { "pattern": "calendar-cli", "argPattern": "^sync\\b" },
              "/bin/date"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Evidence shape
Policy reads `exec-approvals.json` through explicit opt-in, but emits redacted posture records rather than the raw artifact. Socket path/token, command text, resolved paths, timestamps, and approval-session details are omitted.

```json
[
  {
    "kind": "defaults",
    "source": "oc://exec-approvals.json/defaults",
    "security": "full"
  },
  {
    "kind": "agent",
    "source": "oc://exec-approvals.json/agents/sebby",
    "agentId": "sebby",
    "security": "full"
  },
  {
    "kind": "allowlist",
    "source": "oc://exec-approvals.json/agents/sebby/allowlist/#0",
    "agentId": "sebby",
    "pattern": "deploy"
  }
]
```

Findings link a policy requirement to the redacted evidence reference:

```json
{
  "checkId": "policy/exec-approvals-agent-security-unapproved",
  "ocPath": "oc://exec-approvals.json/agents/sebby",
  "requirement": "oc://policy.jsonc/execApprovals/agents/allowSecurity",
  "message": "exec approvals agent 'sebby' uses unapproved security mode 'full'."
}
```

## Real behavior proof
Environment: local WSL checkout at `ce225abf1bfb57039b7cecd492fc458dc5caf4c3`; isolated temp workspace with `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`, `OPENCLAW_HOME`, and `HOME` pointed inside the temp directory. The fixture `exec-approvals.json` included redacted socket path/token fields plus `commandText` and `lastUsedCommand`; those fields are absent from emitted evidence below.

Command path: invoked the Policy plugin CLI command implementation through `pnpm exec tsx` to avoid an unrelated full-repo CLI rebuild failure in `diagnostics-otel`/`protobufjs` during `pnpm openclaw` startup. This exercises `policyCheckCommand` and `policyCompareCommand` from this PR.

